@startuml
title Direct Structured Write

actor User
participant Runtime
participant "Memory API" as API
participant Router
participant Retriever
participant "Entity Canonicalizer" as Canon
participant "Claim Extractor" as CExtract
participant "Claim Reconciler" as CRecon
participant "Task Updater" as TUpdate
participant "Profile Updater" as PUpdate
database DB

User -> Runtime: Explicit fact / preference / task
Runtime -> API: persist_source(turn)
API -> DB: INSERT Source

Runtime -> API: process_memory_write(source_id)
API -> Router: route(latest_turns)
Router --> API: direct_structured_write

API -> Retriever: retrieve_for_update\n(claims, tasks, profile, sources)
Retriever -> DB: SELECT candidate items
Retriever --> API: candidate memory pack

API -> Canon: canonicalize_entities(turn, candidates)
Canon --> API: resolved entities

API -> CExtract: extract_claims(turn, entities,\npredicate_catalog)
CExtract --> API: candidate claims

API -> CRecon: reconcile_claims(candidates,\nexisting claims)
CRecon --> API: claim ops

API -> TUpdate: update_tasks(turn, existing tasks)
TUpdate --> API: task ops

API -> PUpdate: rebuild_profile(existing profile,\npreview(claim ops), preview(task ops))
PUpdate --> API: profile projection

API -> DB: APPLY transaction\n(entities, claim ops, task ops,\nprofile, lineage)
API -> DB: INSERT MemoryRun
API --> Runtime: write complete

note over API, DB
Retrieval-before-update prevents duplicates,
conflicts, and silent overwrites.
end note

@enduml
